The African National Congress says declaring a national state of disaster over the energy crisis will help in ending power cuts by the end of this year. #DStv403 #eNCA  JOHANNESBURG - The African National Congress says declaring a national state of disaster over the energy crisis will help in ending power cuts by the end of this year. The governing party briefed the media at Luthuli House in Johannesburg on Tuesday on the outcomes of its National Executive Committee Lekgotla in Kempton Park. WATCH | Calls for state of disaster on energy crisis at ANC Lekgotla At the same time, the party says ailing municipalities, violent crime and service delivery acceleration - are some of its immediate priorities. eNCA’s Siphamandla Goge has the details in the video above.